---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Foxry"
  description="Privacy Policy for Foxry's applications, plugins, and website."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="legal">
    <article class="container legal-body">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>

      <section>
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how Foxry ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects
          information through our website (foxry-studio.pages.dev) and all applications and plugins
          we develop and publish — including current products such as RetainPulse and Foxry Vault,
          as well as any future services we may offer. By using our services, you agree to the
          practices described in this policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>Shopify Apps</h3>
        <p>
          When you install a Foxry Shopify app, we access certain data through the Shopify API,
          including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Store information (store name, domain, plan)</li>
          <li>Order data (order history, amounts, dates)</li>
          <li>Customer data (names, email addresses, purchase history)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We only request the minimum API scopes required for each app to function.</p>

        <h3>WordPress Plugins</h3>
        <p>
          Our WordPress plugins (such as Foxry Vault) process data entirely on your own WordPress
          server. Form submission data captured by Foxry Vault is stored in your WordPress database
          and is never transmitted to Foxry's servers.
        </p>

        <h3>This Website</h3>
        <p>
          We do not currently use cookies, analytics tools, or any tracking technologies on this
          website. If we introduce analytics or cookies in the future, we will update this policy
          accordingly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the data we collect solely to provide and improve our app functionality, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Customer segmentation and analytics</li>
          <li>Generating reports and dashboards</li>
          <li>Sending notifications you have configured (email, Slack)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> sell, share, or rent your data to third parties. We do
          <strong>not</strong> use your data for advertising purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Data processed by our Shopify apps is stored and processed on Cloudflare's secure global
          infrastructure. All data is encrypted in transit and at rest, and we follow industry
          best practices to protect your information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>

        <h3>Shopify Apps</h3>
        <p>
          When you uninstall a Foxry Shopify app, all data associated with your store is
          permanently deleted from our systems.
        </p>

        <h3>WordPress Plugins</h3>
        <p>
          Since plugin data is stored on your own server, you have full control over its retention.
          Foxry Vault includes a configurable auto-deletion feature for GDPR compliance. When you
          remove the plugin, you may delete the associated data at your discretion.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>Our services integrate with the following third-party providers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Shopify API</strong> — to access store, order, and customer data</li>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — for hosting, data processing, and content delivery</li>
          <li><strong>Resend</strong> — for transactional email delivery (notifications and alerts)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each provider operates under its own privacy policy and data protection practices.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to access, correct, or delete your
          personal data. Under regulations such as the GDPR (EU) and CCPA (California), you may also
          have additional rights including data portability and the right to object to processing.
        </p>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:foxry.support@gmail.com">foxry.support@gmail.com</a>. We will respond to
          your request within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page
          with an updated revision date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:foxry.support@gmail.com">foxry.support@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal { padding: var(--section-py) 0; }

  .legal-body {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .legal-body h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-subtext);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .legal-body section {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-body h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal-body p {
    color: var(--color-subtext);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .legal-body p + p {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }

  .legal-body li {
    color: var(--color-subtext);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin-top: 0.375rem;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .legal-body a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }
</style>
